photographs, Mark A. Vieira sets the record straight, using unpublished production files, financial records, and correspondence to confirm the genius of Thalberg's methods. In addition, this is the first Thalberg biography to utilize both his recorded conversations and the unpublished memoirs of his wife, Norma Shearer. Irving Thalberg is a compelling narrative of power and idealism, revealing for the first time the human being behind the legend.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aben hur.  abiography of irving thalberg.  aco found metro goldwyn mayer at twenty four.  acompelling.  aconfirms genius of thalbergs methods.  acreated classics.  adefinitive.  adied at thirty seven.  afreaks.  agrand hotel.  ahollywood in nineteen twenties.  ahollywoods boy wonder.  ahuman being behind the legend.  aillustrated with rare photographs.  amutiny on the bounty.  aran universal pictures at twenty.  asurvived childhood illness.  atarzan the ape man.  athe good earth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026048140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094511140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945111423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945111/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY